---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import SiteNav from '../components/SiteNav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer';
---

<Layout
  title="Cloud & Google Cloud Architecture"
  description="Design and launch Google Cloud, Vertex AI, and BigQuery foundations with observability, security, and speed."
>
  <SiteNav />

  <main class="bg-zinc-900">
    <section class="py-24 border-b border-zinc-800/60">
      <div class="container mx-auto px-8">
        <div class="max-w-3xl">
          <p class="uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-xs font-semibold text-zinc-500 mb-4">
            cloud & data
          </p>
          <h1 class="text-h1 font-bold text-zinc-50 mb-6">
            Google Cloud foundations built for speed and safety
          </h1>
          <p class="text-lg text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed">
            From Vertex AI pipelines to BigQuery analytics and Firebase backends, we build cloud systems that ship fast,
            stay compliant, and remain simple enough for your team to maintain.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-24 bg-zinc-950 border-b border-zinc-800/60">
      <div class="container mx-auto px-8">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-zinc-50 mb-10">Core capabilities</h2>
        <div class="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
          <div class="card-slate">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-zinc-100 mb-2">Vertex AI pipelines</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-zinc-400">
              Model training, evaluation, and deployment workflows with automated guardrails and rollback.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="card-slate">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-zinc-100 mb-2">BigQuery analytics</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-zinc-400">
              Data warehouses with dbt, scheduled transformations, and Looker Studio dashboards your ops team can trust.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="card-slate">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-zinc-100 mb-2">Firebase / Firestore</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-zinc-400">
              Real-time application backends with security rules, multitenant support, and offline-first UX.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="card-slate">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-zinc-100 mb-2">Cloud Run & Functions</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-zinc-400">
              Serverless APIs, cron jobs, and automation endpoints that scale without upkeep.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="card-slate">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-zinc-100 mb-2">Identity & access</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-zinc-400">
              IAM, service accounts, and workload identity federation configured to keep auditors happy.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="card-slate">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-zinc-100 mb-2">Observability</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-zinc-400">
              Cloud Logging, Metrics, and Grafana dashboards wired from day one so issues surface immediately.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-24 border-b border-zinc-800/60">
      <div class="container mx-auto px-8">
        <div class="grid gap-12 lg:grid-cols-2 items-start">
          <div>
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-zinc-50 mb-6">Engagement blueprint</h2>
            <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-3 text-sm text-zinc-300">
              <li>Audit your current architecture and capture success metrics.</li>
              <li>Design reference architecture diagrams and IaC templates.</li>
              <li>Implement environments with CI/CD, testing, and monitoring hooks.</li>
              <li>Roll out to production with training for your engineers and operators.</li>
            </ol>
            <p class="text-sm text-zinc-400 mt-4">
              Most foundations deploy within four weeks, with optional retained support for continuous optimization.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="card-slate space-y-4">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-zinc-50">Tooling we lean on</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-3 text-sm text-zinc-300">
              <li>Terraform, Pulumi, and Google Cloud Deploy for repeatable infrastructure.</li>
              <li>Cloud Build, GitHub Actions, and Artifact Registry for delivery pipelines.</li>
              <li>Secret Manager + KMS for key rotation and least privilege access.</li>
              <li>Cloud Armor, VPC Service Controls, and BeyondCorp for secure perimeters.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-24 bg-zinc-950 border-b border-zinc-800/60">
      <div class="container mx-auto px-8">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-zinc-50 mb-10">Why operators choose intent solutions io</h2>
        <div class="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">
          <div class="card-slate">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-zinc-100 mb-2">Ship fast, stay sane</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-zinc-400">
              We prioritize workable MVPs with clear handoff docs instead of sprawling multi-quarter projects.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="card-slate">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-zinc-100 mb-2">Operator-first communication</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-zinc-400">
              Weekly syncs, shared Kanban boards, and transparent burn rates keep leadership aligned.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="card-slate">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-zinc-100 mb-2">Compliance ready</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-zinc-400">
              Access policies, logging, and backup strategies tuned for HIPAA, SOC2, PCI, or CJIS environments.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="card-slate">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-zinc-100 mb-2">Handoff without drama</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-zinc-400">
              Internal teams get training, runbooks, and co-working sessions so they feel confident owning the stack.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-24">
      <div class="container mx-auto px-8">
        <div class="grid gap-10 lg:grid-cols-2">
          <div>
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-zinc-50 mb-4">Let’s tune your cloud roadmap</h2>
            <p class="text-sm text-zinc-400 mb-6">
              Bring your current diagrams (or napkin sketches). We’ll highlight gaps, quick wins, and rollout strategies.
            </p>
            <a href="https://calendar.app.google/Wqbt8EJuEh5xvvV58" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn-primary">Book a Discovery Call</a>
          </div>
          <div class="card-slate space-y-4">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-zinc-50">Frequently asked</h3>
            <div>
              <p class="text-sm text-zinc-300 font-medium">Do you only work on Google Cloud?</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-zinc-400">GCP is home base, but we bridge to AWS, Azure, and on-prem systems when needed.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="text-sm text-zinc-300 font-medium">Can you support us after launch?</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-zinc-400">Yes—choose a retainer for monitoring, cost tuning, and roadmap execution.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="text-sm text-zinc-300 font-medium">What about data migrations?</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-zinc-400">We provide migration runbooks, rehearsal plans, and rollback strategies to keep stakeholders calm.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
